  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support for church-led peacebuilding in South Sudan 2019-20</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Support for finalisation and rollout of Capacity Strengthening Framework across ICCs (Malakal, Maban, Renk, Yirol and Bor) 
- Support for improved coordination and information sharing across APP through reflection meetings (Regional ICC forum in Upper Nile)
- Facilitate ICCs to develop and implement Action plans based on the 3 APP Pillars 
- Support ICC Action plan activities
- Women and youth in hard to reach areas including Protection of Civilian camps, engagement in peace building initiatives 
- Bi-annual Upper Nile Regional forum reflection and Peer review in Juba</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The Overall Impact: 
The church in South Sudan is effectively addressing conflict at multiple levels and is making a significant contribution towards building sustainable national peace

Specific project outcomes:
- Enhanced capacity of the church to sustainably address conflict across the country
- Strengthened influence of the Church in providing moral guidance on national peace and reconciliation processes.</narrative>
  </description>
